<|channel>thought
<channel|>I love the rainbows that appear after a summer shower. When the grey clouds part and the golden sun peeks through, a magic bridge forms across the sky.

My favourite rainbows are the ones that look like a giant, colourful smile. I love to spot the bright red stripe at the top and the deep purple at the bottom. Sometimes, if I look very closely, I can see a second, fainter rainbow hiding behind the first one. It looks like a secret mirror!

I like to run into the garden with my wellies on, splashing in the puddles. I imagine that the rainbow is a path leading to a hidden valley filled with pots of gold and friendly dragons. 

Even when the colours fade away, I feel happy. I know that as long as there is rain and sunshine, the magic will always come back to brighten my day. [end of text]


